{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"683b270e-ef8b-4406-b7fc-d804a22a05f9","content":"The template is **not quite ready** for NuGet publishing. Here's a summary:\n\n**✅ Good:**\n- `identity`, `shortName`, `author`, `sourceName`, `classifications`, and `tags` are all present and valid.\n\n**⚠️ Issues to fix:**\n\n1. **Missing `$schema`** — Add `\"$schema\": \"http://json.schemastore.org/template\"` for validation/editor support.\n2. **`Framework` symbol missing `replaces`** — Without `\"replaces\": \"net9.0\"`, the chosen framework value won't actually substitute into your `.csproj`. This is a functional bug.\n3. **Missing `groupIdentity`** — Recommended for NuGet so templates are grouped correctly across versions (e.g., `\"groupIdentity\": \"MyCompany.WebApi.CSharp\"`).\n4. **Placeholder author/identity** — If \"My Company\" / \"MyCompany\" are placeholders, replace them with real values before publishing.\n\nThe `replaces` issue (#2) is the most critical — without it, switching the target framework has no effect.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6463b1d3-b053-46bb-a73d-f031509aefc8","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Let me review this template.json for NuGet publishing readiness. Let me check for required and recommended fields.\n\nKey issues I see:\n\n1. **Missing `$schema`** — Not strictly required, but highly recommended for validation and editor support. Should be `\"$schema\": \"http://json.schemastore.org/template\"`.\n\n2. **Missing `groupIdentity`** — Recommended for NuGet packages so templates can be grouped properly.\n\n3. **Missing `precedence`** — Useful when multiple versions of the same template exist.\n\n4. **Missing `preferNameDirectory`** — Common setting for project templates.\n\n\n5. **`sourceName`**, **`identity`**, **`shortName`**, **`author`**, **`classifications`**, and **`tags`** are all present and properly configured. The main functional gap is the missing `replaces` property on the Framework symbol, which means the parameter won't actually perform substitutions in the project files.\n\n6. **`defaultName`** would be a nice addition but isn't critical.\n\n7. Beyond the `replaces` issue, I should flag that the placeholder values like \"MyCompany\" need to be replaced with real values before publishing, and `groupIdentity` would be recommended for NuGet compatibility. The `$schema` reference is also missing, which is a best practice.","outputTokens":764},"id":"c7fc66aa-4868-4d8c-b5fd-312e39675189","timestamp":"2026-04-04T00:37:09.421Z","parentId":"3d3278f9-151c-4320-b248-b5539c33f40e"}
